{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# LangExtract for Qualitative Research\n",
    "**D-Lab AI Pulse — Module 4: Structured Extraction**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook showcases [LangExtract](https://github.com/google/langextract), a Python library by Google that uses LLMs to extract structured information from unstructured text — purpose-built for the kind of work qualitative researchers actually do.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Version B (Python):** 20-line Colab script using the Gemini API. Batch-processes all responses to CSV. Scales to 1,500 responses with no extra effort. Use this when you need a lightweight, direct pipeline without the grounding features of LangExtract.\n",
    "\n",
    "    "We use two datasets from the workshop:\n",
    "- **Survey responses** (`survey_responses.txt`) — 15 open-ended responses on campus food access barriers\n",
    "- **Interview transcript** (`interview_transcript.txt`) — A 45-minute interview with \"Maya,\" a Berkeley junior\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why LangExtract vs. a raw Gemini API call?\n",
    "\n",
    "| Feature | Raw API call | LangExtract |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Source grounding | ✗ No — you trust the output | ✓ Every extraction maps to an exact text span |\n",
    "| Schema consistency | ✗ Varies across responses | ✓ Enforced via few-shot examples |\n",
    "| Long documents | ✗ Truncated or missed | ✓ Chunked, parallel, multi-pass |\n",
    "| Visualization | ✗ You build it | ✓ Interactive HTML, auto-generated |\n",
    "| Local models | ✗ Usually not | ✓ Ollama built-in |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Seven properties demonstrated below, one section each.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "install",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install LangExtract (run once)\n",
    "%pip install langextract -q"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "imports",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import langextract as lx\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set your Gemini API key\n",
    "# Berkeley users: get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com/\n",
    "os.environ[\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\"] = \"YOUR_API_KEY_HERE\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the workshop data\n",
    "survey_text = Path(\"survey_responses.txt\").read_text()\n",
    "interview_text = Path(\"interview_transcript.txt\").read_text()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Survey responses: {len(survey_text)} characters\")\n",
    "print(f\"Interview transcript: {len(interview_text)} characters\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prop12_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Properties 1 & 2: Precise Source Grounding + Reliable Structured Outputs\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Precise Source Grounding**: Maps every extraction to its exact location in the source text, enabling visual highlighting for easy traceability and verification.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Reliable Structured Outputs**: Enforces a consistent output schema based on your few-shot examples, leveraging controlled generation in supported models like Gemini.\n",
    "\n",
    "We define a few-shot extraction task using two contrasting survey responses. LangExtract learns the schema from these examples and applies it consistently across all 15 responses — and maps every extracted value back to the exact span of text it came from."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "extraction_task",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define few-shot examples — these teach LangExtract your schema\n",
    "# Two contrasting cases: a cost barrier and a stigma/awareness barrier\n",
    "\n",
    "examples = [\n",
    "    lx.data.ExampleData(\n",
    "        text=\"I honestly can't afford to eat out much, and the dining plans are way too \"\n",
    "             \"expensive for what you get. Ramen and peanut butter sandwiches are my diet.\",\n",
    "        extractions=[\n",
    "            lx.data.Extraction(\n",
    "                extraction_class=\"barrier\",\n",
    "                extraction_text=\"can't afford to eat out much, and the dining plans are way too expensive\",\n",
    "                attributes={\n",
    "                    \"barrier_type\": \"Cost\",\n",
    "                    \"level\": \"Institutional\",\n",
    "                    \"sentiment\": \"Negative\",\n",
    "                    \"urgency\": \"High\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    lx.data.ExampleData(\n",
    "        text=\"I didn't realize the university has a food pantry until junior year! \"\n",
    "             \"If someone had told me about it earlier, it would have made such a difference. \"\n",
    "             \"The stigma of asking for help was real, but I'm grateful it exists.\",\n",
    "        extractions=[\n",
    "            lx.data.Extraction(\n",
    "                extraction_class=\"barrier\",\n",
    "                extraction_text=\"didn't realize the university has a food pantry until junior year\",\n",
    "                attributes={\n",
    "                    \"barrier_type\": \"Information\",\n",
    "                    \"level\": \"Intrapersonal\",\n",
    "                    \"sentiment\": \"Mixed\",\n",
    "                    \"urgency\": \"Medium\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            ),\n",
    "            lx.data.Extraction(\n",
    "                extraction_class=\"barrier\",\n",
    "                extraction_text=\"stigma of asking for help was real\",\n",
    "                attributes={\n",
    "                    \"barrier_type\": \"Stigma\",\n",
    "                    \"level\": \"Intrapersonal\",\n",
    "                    \"sentiment\": \"Mixed\",\n",
    "                    \"urgency\": \"Medium\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Extraction schema defined with\", len(examples), \"few-shot examples.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run_extraction",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run extraction over the full survey dataset\n",
    "survey_result = lx.extract(\n",
    "    text_or_documents=survey_text,\n",
    "    prompt_description=(\n",
    "        \"Extract food access barriers from student survey responses. \"\n",
    "        \"For each barrier, identify the barrier type, socio-ecological level \"\n",
    "        \"(intrapersonal / interpersonal / institutional), emotional sentiment, \"\n",
    "        \"and urgency of the student's situation.\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    examples=examples,\n",
    "    model_id=\"gemini-2.0-flash\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Extracted {len(survey_result.extractions)} barriers from the survey data.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "inspect_grounding",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 1: SOURCE GROUNDING\n",
    "# Every extraction has a character-level span pointing back to the original text.\n",
    "# This is what lets us verify (and visualize) exactly what evidence was used.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 1: Precise Source Grounding\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, ext in enumerate(survey_result.extractions[:5]):  # Show first 5\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nExtraction {i+1}:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Text span : '{ext.extraction_text}'\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Char range: [{ext.char_start}, {ext.char_end}]\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Verified  : '{survey_text[ext.char_start:ext.char_end]}'\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Attributes: {ext.attributes}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "inspect_schema",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 2: RELIABLE STRUCTURED OUTPUTS\n",
    "# Every extraction follows the same schema — all four attributes always present,\n",
    "# always drawn from the controlled vocabulary defined by our examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 2: Reliable Structured Outputs\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for ext in survey_result.extractions:\n",
    "    row = {\"evidence\": ext.extraction_text}\n",
    "    row.update(ext.attributes)\n",
    "    rows.append(row)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSchema columns present in ALL {len(df)} extractions: {list(df.columns)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nValue distributions (all within controlled vocabulary):\")\n",
    "print(df[[\"barrier_type\", \"level\", \"sentiment\", \"urgency\"]].value_counts())\n",
    "print(\"\\nFull extraction table:\")\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prop3_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Property 3: Optimized for Long Documents\n",
    "\n",
    "> Overcomes the 'needle-in-a-haystack' challenge of large document extraction by using an optimized strategy of text chunking, parallel processing, and multiple passes for higher recall.\n",
    "\n",
    "A 45-minute interview transcript is far longer than a survey response. A raw API call will either truncate the document or miss passages in the middle. LangExtract splits the document into overlapping chunks, processes them in parallel, and runs multiple passes to maximize recall."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "long_doc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 3: OPTIMIZED FOR LONG DOCUMENTS\n",
    "# Run the same extraction on the full 45-min interview transcript.\n",
    "# extraction_passes=2 means a second pass to catch anything missed the first time.\n",
    "# max_workers=4 enables parallel chunk processing.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 3: Optimized for Long Documents\")\n",
    "print(f\"Interview transcript length: {len(interview_text):,} characters\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "interview_result = lx.extract(\n",
    "    text_or_documents=interview_text,\n",
    "    prompt_description=(\n",
    "        \"Extract food access barriers from this student interview. \"\n",
    "        \"For each barrier mentioned, identify the barrier type, \"\n",
    "        \"socio-ecological level (intrapersonal / interpersonal / institutional), \"\n",
    "        \"emotional sentiment, and urgency.\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    examples=examples,\n",
    "    model_id=\"gemini-2.0-flash\",\n",
    "    extraction_passes=2,   # Second pass increases recall on long documents\n",
    "    max_workers=4          # Parallel chunk processing\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nExtracted {len(interview_result.extractions)} barriers from the interview.\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 3 extractions with source locations:\")\n",
    "for ext in interview_result.extractions[:3]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  [{ext.char_start}:{ext.char_end}] '{ext.extraction_text[:80]}...'\")\n",
    "    print(f\"           barrier_type={ext.attributes.get('barrier_type')}, urgency={ext.attributes.get('urgency')}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prop4_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Property 4: Interactive Visualization\n",
    "\n",
    "> Instantly generates a self-contained, interactive HTML file to visualize and review thousands of extracted entities in their original context.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is what makes verification practical at scale. Instead of reading through a CSV and cross-checking manually, the HTML file highlights every extraction inline in the original document. You can filter by attribute, click to inspect, and immediately see whether the model's interpretation is supported by the text."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "visualize",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 4: INTERACTIVE VISUALIZATION\n",
    "# Generate a self-contained HTML file. Open it in any browser.\n",
    "# Each extracted span is highlighted in the original text.\n",
    "# Filter by barrier_type, level, or urgency to explore the data.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 4: Interactive Visualization\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save both results as JSONL first\n",
    "lx.io.save_annotated_documents(\n",
    "    [survey_result],\n",
    "    output_name=\"survey_extractions.jsonl\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "lx.io.save_annotated_documents(\n",
    "    [interview_result],\n",
    "    output_name=\"interview_extractions.jsonl\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate interactive HTML for the interview (most useful for long docs)\n",
    "lx.visualize(\n",
    "    annotated_documents=[interview_result],\n",
    "    output_file=\"interview_visualization.html\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFiles generated:\")\n",
    "print(\"  survey_extractions.jsonl     — structured data for further analysis\")\n",
    "print(\"  interview_extractions.jsonl  — structured data for further analysis\")\n",
    "print(\"  interview_visualization.html — open in browser to review extractions in context\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nOpen interview_visualization.html in your browser.\")\n",
    "print(\"Each extracted span is highlighted. Filter by barrier_type or urgency.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prop5_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Property 5: Flexible LLM Support\n",
    "\n",
    "> Supports your preferred models, from cloud-based LLMs like the Google Gemini family to local open-source models via the built-in Ollama interface.\n",
    "\n",
    "For IRB-protected interviews or sensitive qualitative data, you may not be able to send data to a cloud API. LangExtract supports local models through Ollama — the same extraction pipeline, with no data leaving your machine.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running the Ollama cell:** Install [Ollama](https://ollama.com/) and pull a model:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "ollama pull llama3.2\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "local_llm",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 5: FLEXIBLE LLM SUPPORT\n",
    "# The only change is model_id. Everything else is identical.\n",
    "# Use this when: data is IRB-protected, contains identifiable health information,\n",
    "# or when institutional policy prohibits sending data to external servers.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 5: Flexible LLM Support\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Cloud (Gemini, Berkeley-licensed) ---\n",
    "print(\"\\nCloud version (Gemini): data goes to Google servers\")\n",
