   "id": "prop6_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Property 6: Adaptable to Any Domain\n",
    "\n",
    "> Define extraction tasks for any domain using just a few examples. LangExtract adapts to your needs without requiring any model fine-tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "We have been extracting *barriers*. Now we switch to extracting *coping strategies* from the same interview — a completely different analytical task, on the same document, using new few-shot examples. No retraining, no configuration beyond the examples."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "new_domain",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 6: ADAPTABLE TO ANY DOMAIN\n",
    "# Switch from extracting barriers to extracting coping strategies.\n",
    "# Same document, same pipeline, new few-shot examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 6: Adaptable to Any Domain\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "coping_examples = [\n",
    "    lx.data.ExampleData(\n",
    "        text=\"I learned pretty quickly that there are a ton of free food events on campus \"\n",
    "             \"if you know where to look. Like, the environmental club — we have meetings on \"\n",
    "             \"Thursdays, and there's always pizza.\",\n",
    "        extractions=[\n",
    "            lx.data.Extraction(\n",
    "                extraction_class=\"coping_strategy\",\n",
    "                extraction_text=\"free food events on campus\",\n",
    "                attributes={\n",
    "                    \"strategy_type\": \"Resource navigation\",\n",
    "                    \"scope\": \"Individual\",\n",
    "                    \"sustainability\": \"Partial\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    lx.data.ExampleData(\n",
    "        text=\"I cook a lot. Rice, beans, eggs, whatever's cheapest. I meal-prep on Sundays.\",\n",
    "        extractions=[\n",
    "            lx.data.Extraction(\n",
    "                extraction_class=\"coping_strategy\",\n",
    "                extraction_text=\"meal-prep on Sundays\",\n",
    "                attributes={\n",
    "                    \"strategy_type\": \"Meal planning\",\n",
    "                    \"scope\": \"Individual\",\n",
    "                    \"sustainability\": \"Partial\"\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "coping_result = lx.extract(\n",
    "    text_or_documents=interview_text,\n",
    "    prompt_description=(\n",
    "        \"Extract coping strategies from this student interview about food insecurity. \"\n",
    "        \"For each strategy, identify the strategy type, whether it is individual \"\n",
    "        \"or collective in scope, and whether it is a sustainable long-term solution \"\n",
    "        \"or a partial workaround.\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    examples=coping_examples,\n",
    "    model_id=\"gemini-2.0-flash\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nExtracted {len(coping_result.extractions)} coping strategies from the same interview.\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nCoping strategies found:\")\n",
    "for ext in coping_result.extractions:\n",
    "    print(f\"  '{ext.extraction_text}'\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   → type={ext.attributes.get('strategy_type')}, \"\n",
    "          f\"scope={ext.attributes.get('scope')}, \"\n",
    "          f\"sustainable={ext.attributes.get('sustainability')}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prop7_header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Property 7: Leverages LLM World Knowledge\n",
    "\n",
    "> Utilize precise prompt wording and few-shot examples to influence how the extraction task may utilize LLM knowledge. The accuracy of any inferred information and its adherence to the task specification are contingent upon the selected LLM, the complexity of the task, the clarity of the prompt instructions, and the nature of the prompt examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is both the most powerful and most epistemically delicate property. By adjusting the prompt, you can ask the LLM to stay purely descriptive (report only what is explicitly stated) or to apply world knowledge (infer implicit barriers that the student may not have named explicitly). The choice is a methodological decision — not a technical one.\n",
    "\n",
    "Below we run the same interview twice with two different prompts and compare what changes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "world_knowledge",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Property 7: LEVERAGES LLM WORLD KNOWLEDGE\n",
    "# Prompt A: Descriptive only — extract only what the student explicitly names.\n",
    "# Prompt B: Inferential — use world knowledge to identify implicit barriers too.\n",
    "# Comparing the two outputs is itself a methodological exercise.\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"PROPERTY 7: Leverages LLM World Knowledge\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "# We use a short excerpt for speed — the passage about the restaurant\n",
    "excerpt = \"\"\"One time — I must have been a freshman — my friends wanted to go to this \n",
    "restaurant, and I went because I didn't want to be like weird about it, and I just \n",
    "ordered like a side salad or something small. And one of my friends was like, \n",
    "'Why are you not getting an entree?' And I froze. I literally didn't know what to say. \n",
    "I couldn't just be like 'because I can't afford it,' so I was like 'oh, I'm not that \n",
    "hungry,' which made it even more awkward. I haven't gone to sit-down restaurants with \n",
    "them very much since then.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "prompt_descriptive = (\n",
    "    \"Extract food access barriers. \"\n",
    "    \"Only extract barriers the student explicitly names or describes. \"\n",
    "    \"Do not infer barriers that are not directly stated.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "prompt_inferential = (\n",
    "    \"Extract food access barriers. \"\n",
    "    \"Include both explicitly stated barriers and barriers implied by the student's \"\n",
    "    \"behavior or emotional responses, drawing on your knowledge of food insecurity \"\n",
    "    \"research to identify what may go unsaid.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "result_a = lx.extract(\n",
    "    text_or_documents=excerpt,\n",
    "    prompt_description=prompt_descriptive,\n",
    "    examples=examples,\n",
    "    model_id=\"gemini-2.0-flash\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "result_b = lx.extract(\n",
    "    text_or_documents=excerpt,\n",
    "    prompt_description=prompt_inferential,\n",
    "    examples=examples,\n",
    "    model_id=\"gemini-2.0-flash\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPrompt A (descriptive only): {len(result_a.extractions)} extractions\")\n",
    "for ext in result_a.extractions:\n",
    "    print(f\"  '{ext.extraction_text}' → {ext.attributes.get('barrier_type')}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPrompt B (inferential): {len(result_b.extractions)} extractions\")\n",
    "for ext in result_b.extractions:\n",
    "    print(f\"  '{ext.extraction_text}' → {ext.attributes.get('barrier_type')}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"METHODOLOGICAL REFLECTION\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "Which prompt is 'right' depends on your research design:\n",
    "\n",
    "  Prompt A (descriptive): Appropriate for content analysis where you want to \n",
    "  stay close to participants' own language. Lower risk of imposing an external \n",
    "  framework. Misses tacit or unsaid barriers.\n",
    "\n",
    "  Prompt B (inferential): Appropriate for theoretically-driven analysis where \n",
    "  you want to apply a known framework to surface what participants don't name. \n",
    "  Requires verification against source text — this is where hallucination risk is \n",
    "  highest. Always cross-check inferred extractions in the visualization.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is not a technical decision. It is a methodological one.\n",
    "\"\"\")"
